The paper discusses a Python library for learning representations of entities and relations in knowledge graphs, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The library also implements state-of-the-art knowledge graph embedding algorithms, which is a topic related to databases (cs.DB). The paper mentions modules for result visualization and mean rank evaluation, which are topics related to natural language processing (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
